-- Pietersen Helps England to 351-5 in South Africa Cricket Test
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-08-04T19:08:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-04/pietersen-helps-england-to-351-5-in-south-africa-cricket-test.html
Kevin Pietersen ’s century helped
England reach 351-5 at stumps on day three of the second cricket
Test against South Africa.  Pietersen is 149 not out at Headingley in Leeds as England
trails by 68 runs in reply to South Africa’s first innings total
of 419 all out.  Andrew Strauss  scored 37 and Matt Prior is 20
not out.  South Africa leads 1-0 in the three-game contest. The
Proteas can replace England at the top of the International
Cricket Council Test rankings by winning the series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
